Q.1 What is the default value of Array for different data types?
Ans. integer = 0
     string = null
     floating num = 0.0
     Boolean = false
     character = null	
Q.2 Can you pass the negative number in Array size?
Ans. no 
Q.3  Where does Array stored in JVM memory ?
Ans. if create using 
        int array[] = new Int[5];
         then this in heap memory 
     else 
          int array[] = {10,4,25,35,7,85,5};
          this in stack memory 
Q.4 what are the disadvantages of Array?
Ans. fixed size 
     Array store only same type of data 
     no Built in methods for operations like searching , sorting resizing 
Q.5 what is an anonymous Array in java ? Give an example ?
Ans.  anonymous Array that created without assigned to a variable it use only for single time in method argument 
Q.6 what are the different way to traverse an array in java ?
Ans.  there are three way to traverse an array 
      using while loop , for loop , Foreach loop
      for(int i:arr){
System.out.println(i);
}


